WEBVTT

01:21.090 --> 01:23.193
as a joy to be with you this morning.

01:23.853 --> 01:26.717
Let me ask if you would open your bibles to the Book of Romans.

01:27.598 --> 01:29.941
Matthew, Mark, Luke, John, Acts, Romans.

01:30.241 --> 01:33.265
And if you will, just kind of hold your finger there for a couple minutes.

01:33.986 --> 01:42.257
Before I launch into this, I just got to say, just thank you to Philip, to Laura, and to all the folks who led us in worship this morning.

01:42.277 --> 01:44.139
Can you guys just say thank you to those folks?

01:44.199 --> 01:46.642
Just come back.

01:49.954 --> 02:03.676
So last several weeks, we've been talking about this series called Focus, which is a way for us, all as members of Concord to focus on the things that are vital to us as we move into a new season of our ministry.

02:04.117 --> 02:09.165
And just a quick update before we launch into today's message, which is the final message in this series.

02:10.387 --> 02:17.618
You know, first of these weeks, several weeks, a couple weeks ago, we were talking about the importance of focusing on our mission.

02:17.954 --> 02:21.318
And so we talked about that passage in Hebrews chapter 12, the first couple of verses.

02:21.959 --> 02:41.842
Therefore, since we have so great a cloud of witnesses surrounding us, let us also lay aside every weight in the sin that so easily entangles us and let us run with endurance or patience, the race that is set before us, that race that God gives to every person, that God gives to every church, that race is about our mission.

02:42.658 --> 02:43.679
And we can never forget it.

02:43.719 --> 02:48.444
At Concord, it's the same mission, really, that any faithful church anywhere on the globe has.

02:49.225 --> 02:53.049
And that is to make disciples, to make disciples everywhere.

02:54.050 --> 03:02.339
And so last week as a second in that series, we said, it's not just about focusing right now on our mission, we also need to focus on ourselves.

03:03.300 --> 03:06.964
So like Paul said to Timothy, pay close attention to yourself.

03:07.684 --> 03:09.266
And we talked about the fact that

03:09.538 --> 03:17.108
You know, for all of us, if we're going to make disciples everywhere, then we can't ever get very far away from the importance of being disciples.

03:18.109 --> 03:26.841
The word disciple means to be a learner, and it implies that we are constantly learning from Jesus, being transformed by Jesus.

03:27.101 --> 03:34.872
This is not just something at becoming a Christian, it's not just a one-time thing that we achieve the minimal entry requirements for heaven, and that's where it stops.

03:34.892 --> 03:36.594
I mean, this is a lifestyle.

03:37.282 --> 03:44.531
And when we are people who are being constantly transformed by Jesus, there is a powerful impact from that.

03:44.651 --> 03:46.774
Our neighbors see it, our coworkers see it.

03:47.315 --> 03:48.656
It's hard to explain away.

03:49.598 --> 03:53.723
So we need to focus in these days on our mission.

03:53.743 --> 03:54.324
We need to focus.

03:54.384 --> 03:55.866
I need to focus on myself.

03:56.747 --> 04:02.514
Now this morning, the third in this series, I think we also need to focus on our message.

04:03.266 --> 04:07.130
And the passage or the text that I want to start with this morning is from the Book of Romans.

04:07.490 --> 04:08.471
You're holding your finger there.

04:08.511 --> 04:20.483
The first chapter, the 16th verse where the Bible says, Paul says, I'm not ashamed of the gospel for it's the power of God for salvation to everyone who believes to the Jew first and also to the Greek.

04:21.905 --> 04:24.928
Now, I want to talk to you this morning about the gospel.

04:25.829 --> 04:26.770
That's our message.

04:28.131 --> 04:30.834
That's the message of the Christian church all over the world.

04:32.194 --> 04:38.482
And you may say, JoJo, why in the world are you gonna talk to us about our message, or about the gospel?

04:39.183 --> 04:44.108
I mean, we have heard the gospel for the last nine years every Sunday.

04:44.129 --> 04:45.210
We know the gospel.

04:45.230 --> 04:46.792
I mean, maybe you're thinking that.

04:47.252 --> 04:48.494
But first, let me just say this.

04:48.714 --> 04:54.421
Can I just say praise God that we have heard the gospel every Sunday for the last nine years?

04:55.122 --> 05:00.609
There are places, lots of churches in this world where you can go a lifetime and not hear the gospel.

05:00.629 --> 05:01.810
We've heard the gospel

05:01.890 --> 05:04.233
every Sunday for the last nine years.

05:04.294 --> 05:07.178
We've all been blessed by it.

05:07.198 --> 05:17.774
But there's several reasons I still think that we need to stop and focus, pay attention to, listen to the gospel, to focus on our message.

05:18.895 --> 05:22.601
Now part of that is because you never get any part of life.

05:22.621 --> 05:26.246
You never get very far away from the fundamentals or you shouldn't.

05:28.169 --> 05:31.474
I mean, I looked at the calendar this week and

05:31.938 --> 05:36.903
confirmed that it is 10 Saturdays from now that college football will start.

05:39.186 --> 05:45.032
And so all of the women in the room are rolling their eyes in early, and all the guys are doing cartwheels inwardly.

05:46.073 --> 06:01.810
But between now and then, all these coaches all over America, now it's even earlier, high school, and all these coaches all over America are getting their teams together, you know, they're beginning to talk about what they need to get ready for, and I'm just gonna guarantee you that every coach, every coach in America is gonna

06:02.210 --> 06:06.354
in his first practices, he is gonna go back to the fundamentals.

06:07.115 --> 06:08.076
He's gonna talk about it.

06:08.096 --> 06:09.597
Well, here's how you block.

06:09.637 --> 06:10.919
Here's how you tackle.

06:11.459 --> 06:23.030
And somebody, somewhere I do that old Vince Lombardi speech, he'll hold up the football, he'll say, this is a football because people can never get very far away from the basics.

06:25.172 --> 06:30.898
Now, another reason I think we ought to talk about the message, our message, focus on our message is because

06:31.330 --> 06:37.257
Increasingly in our world, there is some opposition to sharing the gospel.

06:37.278 --> 06:37.938
We all know this.

06:39.360 --> 06:58.104
Now, I saw a statistic this past week from the new head of evangelism for the Georgia Baptist Mission Board, a guy named Levi Skipper said 47% of Christian millennials today believe it's wrong to share the gospel.

06:58.865 --> 06:59.826
I don't know.

07:00.034 --> 07:01.917
I haven't studied that statistic.

07:01.937 --> 07:03.519
I don't know all of their reasons.

07:05.001 --> 07:23.810
I would guess it has something to do with what's going on in our world and the fact that in our world today, that whether it's because of political correctness or postmodernism or whatever it is, in our world today, the very idea that you would challenge somebody else's worldview instead of affirming it, which brings a level of offense is just out of bounds.

07:24.050 --> 07:25.973
So I suppose it has something to do with that.

07:26.053 --> 07:29.458
It may be a great reason for us to go back.

07:30.754 --> 07:32.716
and focus on our message, the gospel.

07:33.958 --> 07:42.447
But I need to tell you this morning that the primary reason that I want to talk about our message, the gospel, is more personal than either of those things.

07:44.189 --> 07:55.883
It's because in my life, I read this text where Paul says, I'm not ashamed of the gospel and I've just got to say with all honesty, I've never been ashamed of the gospel.

07:55.903 --> 07:58.866
But in my life, there have been seasons and times when I have

08:00.290 --> 08:02.213
been less than impressed with the gospel.

08:05.659 --> 08:08.384
I hope you're better than that, but it's a truth.

08:10.147 --> 08:18.461
In my life, there have been seasons and times when the good news has to me seemed like old news.

08:20.364 --> 08:26.514
Maybe because I've been a Christian most of my life now, a long time, and anything that you

08:26.626 --> 08:29.028
relate to for a long time, you know, like a marriage.

08:29.068 --> 08:31.270
Sometimes you can begin to take for granted.

08:31.290 --> 08:35.194
And I think from time to time, I've been guilty of doing that with the gospel.

08:35.234 --> 08:41.921
I hope you haven't, but I see a lot of Christians and speak to a lot of Christians who this is a challenge for them.

08:41.941 --> 08:55.794
And so this morning, if it's a challenge for you, if for some reason you've lost touch with the reality of how awesome the gospel is, and we all do sometimes, then I want to reconnect

08:56.226 --> 09:02.253
for you, the wonder of what our message actually is.

09:03.654 --> 09:19.412
And if there's somebody in the room this morning and I would guess there may be, who even though you've been here maybe for nine years and you've heard the gospel spoken, you know the truth about this is that you can hear the gospel spoken and spoken well and it has been spoken well here.

09:21.014 --> 09:24.978
But there is something that is not human about this event when a person actually

09:25.058 --> 09:26.479
hears for the first time.

09:27.921 --> 09:41.314
There is something that only God controls when the scales fall off of someone's eyes, and even though you've heard the words so many times before, today can be your day when you hear the gospel for the first time.

09:41.394 --> 09:43.956
My prayer is today can be your day.

09:45.998 --> 09:50.102
So let's launch into this, how we focus on our message.

09:51.143 --> 09:53.746
And I want to do that by beginning with a couple of questions.

09:54.338 --> 09:56.262
And the first one is the gospel.

09:56.282 --> 10:06.541
I mean, the central Christian message and our message here at Concord is the gospel just a command for me to behave myself.

10:09.247 --> 10:17.362
Now, you may laugh, but listen, I mean, when I was a kid growing up at home, my mom, my dad, they had this look.

10:18.882 --> 10:21.445
You don't have a mom and dad like this, you know.

10:21.465 --> 10:28.935
Yeah, this looks like when I was misbehaving in church or I was misbehaving someplace in a public setting, I mean, my mom and dad had this look and they didn't require words.

10:28.975 --> 10:31.238
They could just, you know, just give me this look like that.

10:31.298 --> 10:35.643
And it was like some people call this the stink eye, but it's like, you know, you all know what I'm talking about.

10:36.624 --> 10:37.946
You all know what that look means.

10:39.288 --> 10:40.269
You don't have to have words.

10:40.309 --> 10:42.972
That look means JoJo, behave yourself.

10:44.514 --> 10:45.656
Now mom and dad had that look.

10:45.696 --> 10:47.378
My teachers at school had that look.

10:48.002 --> 10:53.910
I could be doing something, thinking they're not even paying attention, and then they're looking over those glasses, you know, and they're looking at me like that.

10:53.971 --> 10:56.574
It says, JoJo, behave yourself.

10:58.217 --> 11:01.001
And then I go to church and the preachers that we had.

11:01.281 --> 11:02.262
Now they didn't have a look.

11:03.083 --> 11:06.709
And for goodness sake, they certainly didn't accomplish this with no words.

11:06.889 --> 11:08.151
They had lots of words.

11:08.551 --> 11:11.235
But the preachers that we had, they were always saying the same thing.

11:11.255 --> 11:16.082
It was like they were telling me to say, you know, don't lie, don't cheat, don't steal.

11:16.194 --> 11:19.340
You know, don't have sex outside marriage, don't do drugs.

11:19.360 --> 11:28.979
And it's like, to me, it was like every Sunday, it was just a different version of the same message, JoJo, behave yourself.

11:28.999 --> 11:35.872
Now, I'm not here today to say that, you know, if you're a young person today, don't go home and say, that preacher said, I don't have to behave myself.

11:35.892 --> 11:36.914
That's not the point.

11:37.762 --> 11:48.535
We can all take a look at the news or people we know and find somebody who did not control their lust or did not control their greed or didn't control their selfishness and it's ruined their lives.

11:49.956 --> 11:53.040
Listen, the Bible says, many are the sorrows of the wicked.

11:53.060 --> 11:56.404
That's the case, but I'm not here to say we shouldn't behave ourselves.

11:57.365 --> 12:05.074
I'm just here to say this morning that that is not the central message of the Christian church and certainly that is not the gospel.

12:06.722 --> 12:18.395
Listen, I have to say that because there are a lot of people like me who have come to church week after week and somehow it's gotten lodged in their brain that this is what it's all about.

12:19.276 --> 12:24.241
And I just need to say, if you went to school to learn how to be wrong, you couldn't have been more wrong.

12:24.602 --> 12:26.704
That's absolutely wrong.

12:27.225 --> 12:30.288
The gospel is not a command to behave yourself.

12:31.810 --> 12:35.634
I need to say this because there are so many people who believe that God loves people

12:35.746 --> 12:37.568
if they behave themselves.

12:38.689 --> 12:44.535
And there are lots of people who believe that heaven is a reward for people who behave themselves.

12:45.816 --> 12:50.261
That's absolutely wrong and it certainly is not the gospel.

12:52.143 --> 12:55.066
Listen, the gospel is not just a command to behave yourself.

12:55.146 --> 12:57.188
And I need to ask this question as well.

12:58.749 --> 13:03.474
Is the gospel just good advice?

13:04.066 --> 13:09.975
I mean, as it regards the issue of eternity, is that the gospel?

13:09.995 --> 13:12.098
I'm good advice like don't end up in hell.

13:13.180 --> 13:14.201
That would be good advice.

13:17.085 --> 13:26.379
You know, if I'm driving down the road someplace and I see a sign that warns me, says, bridge out or dead end or something like that, that's good advice.

13:26.500 --> 13:28.002
I mean, something I should pay attention to.

13:28.022 --> 13:30.866
I don't want to just go, you know,

13:30.978 --> 13:33.602
off the edge of some bridge that's out and end up in the river.

13:33.622 --> 13:38.249
I mean, that's good advice, but is that good news?

13:40.372 --> 13:44.799
I mean, the word gospel means good news.

13:46.742 --> 13:52.931
And listen, preachers give, as it regards eternity, preachers give good advice.

13:52.971 --> 13:57.458
I'll say great advice all the time, and they should, and we should listen to it.

13:59.042 --> 14:00.844
Because there are important things that stick.

14:02.647 --> 14:18.748
I mean, the analogy I use is if you go out here in the yard today and there's a flower out there, some little flower that draws its life from the sun, like all things on the planet, it draws its sustenance, it draws its energy from the sun.

14:18.788 --> 14:23.154
And so here's this little flower who decides on a particular day, you know what, that's just not my opinion.

14:24.418 --> 14:26.862
That is too narrow and confining for me.

14:27.263 --> 14:28.905
That's not what I believe anymore.

14:29.026 --> 14:36.117
And so this little flower decides to pull a piece of cardboard over its head and it's, I am no longer going to receive any sustenance from the sun.

14:36.157 --> 14:44.451
I'm going to cut myself off from that source because I don't need that anymore.

14:44.471 --> 14:47.837
What's going to happen to that flower?

14:47.857 --> 14:50.962
I mean, it may not be today, it may not be tomorrow, but you know,

14:53.218 --> 15:05.073
At some point, not very long, his preference won't matter, its belief won't matter, its sincerity won't matter, reality will matter.

15:07.896 --> 15:22.194
You know, in the scripture, John, the first chapter, there's a passage where the writer, the apostle John says, in the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.

15:22.498 --> 15:24.261
The same was in the beginning with God.

15:24.321 --> 15:26.123
All things were made by him.

15:26.203 --> 15:31.531
And apart from him was not anything made that was made in him was life.

15:35.097 --> 15:36.579
In him was life.

15:38.522 --> 15:44.150
Now, you read that text and you may read over it quickly and think, well, okay, I get it, but no, listen, stop and think.

15:44.410 --> 15:48.156
This is not saying that Jesus, it's not just saying that Jesus was alive.

15:48.216 --> 15:49.618
Of course he was alive.

15:50.562 --> 15:53.906
What John is saying is that life is in him.

15:55.268 --> 16:06.783
What John is saying is that like for that little flower that draws its sustenance from the sun, Jesus is like some great son that sits at the center of all things.

16:07.384 --> 16:09.947
That he is the source of life.

16:10.207 --> 16:15.474
It's saying that all life emanates from him and only from him.

16:16.130 --> 16:21.899
So when I, like that little flower decide, I'm gonna sever myself or cut myself off from him.

16:21.979 --> 16:24.723
There is nothing good that can come from that.

16:26.526 --> 16:31.073
Now should we heed that advice, absolutely we should heed that advice.

16:32.956 --> 16:36.281
But I just need to say again, we're talking here about the gospel.

16:36.361 --> 16:39.746
The word gospel means good news.

16:42.570 --> 16:45.074
This may be the backdrop to the gospel.

16:46.626 --> 16:55.797
This may be, while there's such a huge urgency about the gospel, but in and of itself, good advice is not good news.

16:55.857 --> 16:58.320
The gospel means good news.

17:00.403 --> 17:03.166
So what is the gospel?

17:04.869 --> 17:06.571
What is this good news?

17:06.831 --> 17:15.762
I'm gonna talk this morning about just a few simple things that I think sometimes that we as believers forget, and I think many times people who are not yet believers

17:16.162 --> 17:18.965
think they've heard the gospel but have not yet heard.

17:21.628 --> 17:23.050
I'm going to have about three quick things.

17:23.170 --> 17:24.852
One is the gospel is good news.

17:24.952 --> 17:27.615
It's something that's true about God.

17:27.655 --> 17:32.620
It's also something that's true about what God has done.

17:32.660 --> 17:34.722
And it's something that's true about my future.

17:35.163 --> 17:38.346
Those are the three things we're going to touch on this morning for just a few minutes.

17:38.386 --> 17:45.234
And so the first one, when we say something that's true about God, the gospel, the good news, our message to the world,

17:46.114 --> 17:50.160
is that God is amazingly good.

17:52.343 --> 18:00.996
You know, billions of people in the world today, billions, I don't need to name the religion, billions of people worship a God, at least a concept of God.

18:02.298 --> 18:06.644
And their idea of him is that he is like the ultimate scorekeeper.

18:08.748 --> 18:11.111
I mean, he is, he is aloof.

18:12.193 --> 18:13.074
He's remote.

18:14.274 --> 18:14.935
He's cold.

18:14.955 --> 18:17.278
He takes no initiative to reach out to me.

18:17.318 --> 18:19.702
He's the ultimate score keeper.

18:22.926 --> 18:23.868
Is that what God is like?

18:28.414 --> 18:42.194
You know, if I turn on the TV today or watch anything that's produced by just our culture, very often the picture that is portrayed of God is a picture of someone who wants to subtract from my life.

18:43.970 --> 18:54.264
It's someone that if I follow his dictates and his rules that it's going to minimize my potential in my future, the things that I might take part in and things that I might enjoy.

18:54.324 --> 18:56.146
And I just need to ask, is that?

18:58.389 --> 19:01.353
Is God just the ultimate killjoy?

19:01.413 --> 19:03.516
Is that what God is like?

19:06.260 --> 19:11.026
You know, in the New Testament world, when Jesus spoke

19:11.266 --> 19:15.712
to the people around him, they had hundreds of gods, ideas about God.

19:16.974 --> 19:27.328
And if you studied Greek and Roman culture, you know with your mythology, you know that the ideas of the gods, they might have worshiped at Ephesus or different places in the New Testament.

19:27.348 --> 19:34.859
You see, you mentioned these are gods are more like soap opera characters than they are the real God.

19:36.040 --> 19:40.146
I mean, they are indifferent to human beings.

19:40.450 --> 19:42.273
They're selfish, they're petty.

19:44.837 --> 19:54.693
And I just need to say this morning that the picture of God that Jesus gave the world was 180 degrees different from these things, all these things.

19:56.736 --> 20:08.274
If you want to this morning with me, open your Bible to the gospel of Luke in the 15th chapter to what is a very familiar passage, probably to many of us this morning, the story we call the prodigal son.

20:10.242 --> 20:12.486
This is Jesus' picture of God.

20:14.188 --> 20:17.454
And you know the story, how the Bible says a certain man had two sons.

20:19.217 --> 20:24.225
Verse 11, the younger of them said to his father, Father, give me the share of the estate that falls to me.

20:24.265 --> 20:27.510
And so he divided his wealth between them.

20:28.652 --> 20:33.239
So I like to say that this younger son says, Dad, I know you're not dead, but let's pretend that you are.

20:34.361 --> 20:37.426
And so you give me what's coming to me and you know the story that he took

20:37.538 --> 20:42.145
this inheritance and he went off to a far country because he had been planning this for a long time.

20:43.848 --> 20:49.356
And he went down and he, the Bible says he squandered it with something called loose living.

20:49.396 --> 20:50.738
We don't need to go into details.

20:52.541 --> 20:56.868
And it wasn't very long before a famine arose in that land and he began to be in need.

20:57.990 --> 21:00.754
So much so that he began to be desperate.

21:02.114 --> 21:10.123
And the scripture says, Jesus tells the story that at some particular point, he came to, verse 17, I think it is, he says, he came to his senses.

21:11.744 --> 21:19.653
And he begins to imagine, thinking his mind, he says, you know, really, even the slaves in my father's house have at least something to eat.

21:19.753 --> 21:25.960
And he begins to fashion in his head a little speech that he could give to his dad if he were to go back.

21:26.000 --> 21:28.402
Father, I'm no longer worthy to be called your son.

21:29.784 --> 21:31.826
Make me as one of your hired servants.

21:32.002 --> 21:33.524
begins the way back.

21:35.526 --> 21:37.088
I don't know exactly how this happened.

21:37.128 --> 21:48.702
I just know enough about dads and moms and kids to know that this is something that this dad has been hoping for for how long the boy's been gone.

21:51.065 --> 22:01.938
And I just imagine him sitting on the front porch and seeing a little cloud of dust and some person making his way up the road a long way off and, you know, parents can tell their kid.

22:03.650 --> 22:05.972
long before they ever see the face.

22:08.375 --> 22:19.086
And so this guy leaps off the porch, and he sprints down to where this boy is, and the boy starts into his speech, father, I'm no longer worthy, and the father says, shut up.

22:19.546 --> 22:24.491
He says, go, get the best robe and put it on him.

22:24.531 --> 22:31.058
Bring sandals for his feet, put a ring on his finger, kill the fatted calf, because this boy of mine is

22:31.234 --> 22:34.920
He was dead as alive again, and so it's time to celebrate.

22:36.422 --> 22:43.193
Do you understand that when Jesus told that story, the Father in that story, He's giving us a picture of God?

22:45.877 --> 22:53.870
And the picture of God that He gives us is not a picture of a God who is only concerned about behavior.

22:55.853 --> 22:56.754
I mean, if any

22:56.834 --> 23:00.380
kid has ever scored a zero on the behavior self scale.

23:00.640 --> 23:02.644
This boy scored a zero.

23:04.487 --> 23:10.536
But this is a picture of a God who is not just concerned about my behavior, he's concerned about me.

23:12.600 --> 23:19.371
And it's a picture of a God who does not desire to bless only those who deserve it.

23:21.454 --> 23:23.698
As I said, this boy does not deserve it.

23:26.306 --> 23:32.353
It's a picture of a God who desires to bless even those who deserve the opposite.

23:32.553 --> 23:33.314
Praise God.

23:34.776 --> 23:35.336
Praise God.

23:36.097 --> 23:38.179
He's not just concerned for my behavior.

23:38.279 --> 23:39.481
He's concerned for me.

23:39.821 --> 23:43.045
He doesn't just desire to bless me if I deserve it.

23:43.185 --> 23:46.609
He desires to bless me when I deserve the opposite.

23:47.750 --> 23:50.613
It's a picture of a God who's not just real.

23:52.075 --> 23:54.738
He's not just powerful.

23:56.450 --> 23:57.772
some versions of God.

23:57.872 --> 23:59.174
He's not just wise.

24:01.777 --> 24:02.659
He's not just holy.

24:02.739 --> 24:03.540
He's all those things.

24:03.600 --> 24:04.141
He's real.

24:04.221 --> 24:05.062
He's powerful.

24:05.122 --> 24:06.163
He's wise.

24:06.424 --> 24:07.185
He's holy.

24:07.425 --> 24:08.066
He's good.

24:08.647 --> 24:10.629
He's amazingly good.

24:11.511 --> 24:13.814
This is what Jesus is saying to us.

24:14.234 --> 24:17.799
And it's a part of the good news that Jesus gave the world.

24:17.839 --> 24:25.650
And it fell upon the world like a thunderclap in contrast to everything they'd heard before, understood before.

24:25.922 --> 24:31.530
that the one who sits at the center of all things is not indifferent to me.

24:31.890 --> 24:47.851
The one who sits at the center of all things is not only concerned with whether I deserve something, but the one who sits at the center of all things is not just real, not just wise, not just powerful, not just holy, not even just good.

24:48.192 --> 24:50.335
He is off the chain, good.

24:50.895 --> 24:53.459
He is beyond words, good.

24:53.499 --> 24:55.762
He is amazingly good.

24:57.346 --> 24:58.727
This is part of the good news.

24:59.088 --> 25:00.089
It's not all of it.

25:00.109 --> 25:04.653
It's just part of the good news that is our privilege to give the world.

25:06.415 --> 25:09.458
Every day, every week.

25:09.478 --> 25:10.399
And it's just the beginning.

25:10.419 --> 25:12.821
It's like I said, we're gonna talk about three things today.

25:12.841 --> 25:17.786
And the first one is the good news is something true about God that God is amazingly good.

25:19.188 --> 25:20.349
Beyond description, good.

25:20.369 --> 25:25.714
And because He's amazingly good, the Bible also says,

25:26.914 --> 25:33.185
The good news is about something God has done out of his goodness as a result of his goodness.

25:35.208 --> 25:39.195
You know, when I was a pastor, I had a, I was a guy in our church, his name was Cliff.

25:41.318 --> 25:52.978
Cliff went to the, to the doctor when Cliff had cancer and he went to the doctor one time and as he did, he had told so many people in the church, a bunch of us, you know, that he was going to get news on this particular day.

25:56.642 --> 26:00.628
So we were all waiting and he was going to send out an email to all most of the church really.

26:01.930 --> 26:06.156
So at a particular moment, I turned around and on my screen on my computer, the email popped up.

26:07.058 --> 26:13.728
And I don't know how he did this, but he made it in a font that was so big that there was not room for anything else on the screen.

26:13.748 --> 26:15.551
The font took up the entire screen.

26:16.011 --> 26:17.213
And it's just three words.

26:17.914 --> 26:20.338
Praise the Lord.

26:23.138 --> 26:26.883
Because Cliff had gone to the doctor and heard the most beautiful words in the English language.

26:28.826 --> 26:29.467
Cancer-free.

26:31.830 --> 26:37.838
I mean, for Cliff, it was not about going to the doctor and trying to keep from getting sick.

26:37.858 --> 26:41.563
The reason those words were so beautiful to him.

26:41.583 --> 26:43.826
It wasn't about trying to keep from getting sick.

26:43.866 --> 26:47.731
They were beautiful because he already was sick.

26:47.751 --> 26:52.658
And it was like there was some thing in his body that it was like a freight train that already left the station.

26:52.866 --> 26:58.712
And unless somebody could stop that freight train that it was going to take him out, he knew this.

26:59.353 --> 27:01.895
He needed something to stop that freight train.

27:01.915 --> 27:06.400
It's like some judgment that was already working its way through his cells and through his body.

27:06.440 --> 27:11.865
He needed somebody to stop this, to vaporize this, to obliterate this.

27:11.905 --> 27:13.947
And he heard those words cancer-free.

27:14.228 --> 27:16.610
And it was the best news he could imagine.

27:19.193 --> 27:20.594
You know, for all of us,

27:21.378 --> 27:22.920
The issue is not cancer.

27:22.940 --> 27:25.302
The Bible says the issue is something called sin.

27:25.342 --> 27:26.584
It's not a physical reality.

27:26.624 --> 27:28.326
It's a, it's deeper than that.

27:30.348 --> 27:48.609
It's that part of me that says that even though, even though God gives me every heartbeat, God gives me every breath, it makes sense to me that I would shove him to the edges of my life and treat him as absolutely irrelevant.

27:48.629 --> 27:49.650
That makes sense to me.

27:52.994 --> 28:07.691
Sin is that part of me that says that even though God is the maker of all things and my maker, that I will take that place as the center of the universe, everything needs to revolve around me.

28:07.851 --> 28:09.873
God himself should serve me.

28:10.134 --> 28:12.977
I get angry at God when he does not serve me.

28:13.778 --> 28:17.022
This makes sense to me because of something called sin.

28:17.042 --> 28:18.083
It's rebellion.

28:18.123 --> 28:20.946
It lives in every one of us and the Bible sits.

28:22.658 --> 28:27.162
There is a judgment associated with it like a freight train that's already left the station.

28:28.944 --> 28:30.426
And every one of our lives.

28:32.047 --> 28:37.333
So what Paul says when he says in Romans 623, the wage is the consequences of sin is death.

28:39.795 --> 28:47.683
But listen, this God who is so amazingly good, this God who has no obligation to even pay attention to me.

28:49.565 --> 28:50.706
And what am I?

28:50.978 --> 28:54.622
some tiny infinitesimal speck in a whole but universal.

28:54.882 --> 28:56.844
Why is he to even pay attention to me?

28:59.607 --> 29:08.856
But this God chooses not only to pay attention to me, the Bible says in Romans the 5th chapter and the 8th verse.

29:08.876 --> 29:13.801
But God demonstrates his own love for us in that while we were yet sinners Christ died for us.

29:14.121 --> 29:15.522
He is not indifferent to me.

29:15.823 --> 29:19.186
The Bible says that this amazingly good God

29:19.394 --> 29:21.357
He doesn't just pay attention to me.

29:21.598 --> 29:38.187
He steps into my place and he receives in the person of his son the judgment that I so richly deserve, which is why in Romans the eighth chapter, the first verse, Paul says, therefore now there is no condemnation.

29:38.287 --> 29:39.730
Listen to those words.

29:42.146 --> 29:47.094
This condemnation that I deserve absolutely, God has vaporized it.

29:47.114 --> 29:48.536
He's obliterated.

29:48.596 --> 29:54.625
There is now no condemnation, no hint, no whiff, no bathtub ring.

29:54.645 --> 29:56.187
It's like it's gone.

29:59.032 --> 30:11.090
Do you remember what it was like when you were in school and how you got an assignment from a teacher that you had six weeks to do this project you're supposed to do for science or whatever it is and you hadn't done

30:11.874 --> 30:15.137
Nothing.

30:15.157 --> 30:16.078
Maybe you're better than me.

30:16.118 --> 30:18.981
Maybe you never did this, but I do.

30:19.001 --> 30:24.026
You know what it's like to lay down at night and close your eyes and you've got an assignment like that.

30:24.146 --> 30:30.913
Do the next morning you hadn't done nothing and you say it is like judgment is coming tomorrow and I deserve it.

30:32.995 --> 30:39.762
You close your eyes with a sense of impending doom over you and you open your eyes the next morning as a funny glow in the room.

30:41.282 --> 30:45.669
And you rub your eyes and walk over to the window and there's six inches of snow on the ground.

30:45.689 --> 30:47.673
It's like hallelujah.

30:47.693 --> 30:48.414
I'm saved.

30:48.694 --> 30:49.756
You all know that feeling?

30:50.377 --> 30:51.159
You ever been there?

30:52.260 --> 30:59.633
Well, look, this is not just for a day, that sense of judgment being obliterated and vaporized and gone forever.

30:59.853 --> 31:01.155
It's not just for a day.

31:01.436 --> 31:04.962
It's forever and ever and ever and ever.

31:04.982 --> 31:06.144
Praise God for that.

31:06.184 --> 31:07.506
Is that good news?

31:08.002 --> 31:11.206
Listen, why would you not say yes to that?

31:12.247 --> 31:13.088
Why would you not?

31:14.930 --> 31:23.940
Listen, the gospel that our message is not just good advice, it's not just a command to behave yourself.

31:24.300 --> 31:27.224
This is the best news the planet has ever heard.

31:28.905 --> 31:31.969
That God is not just good, He's amazingly good.

31:32.449 --> 31:36.594
And that out of that goodness that God has chosen, not just to pay attention to me,

31:36.962 --> 31:45.772
But to stand in my place and take my judgment and evaporate and obliterate forever the judgment that I deserve so rich.

31:48.635 --> 31:51.298
But this is not all of it.

31:51.498 --> 31:53.280
The good news is also.

31:54.982 --> 31:57.344
The good news is also just one other thing.

31:57.364 --> 32:02.070
And that's a truth about my future and your future.

32:04.232 --> 32:06.194
Listen, when I think about this, I think about

32:08.962 --> 32:10.784
This passage will touch in just a second.

32:10.844 --> 32:16.992
I think about my dad who, dad's been gone about three years, died in 2015.

32:17.012 --> 32:22.739
And the last years of my dad's life were just no fun.

32:25.442 --> 32:28.366
Some of you have older parents, you know exactly what I'm talking about.

32:31.730 --> 32:34.754
Mom passed away in 2006 and my dad never got over that.

32:37.197 --> 32:38.098
And his life,

32:38.370 --> 32:41.695
for the last few years was just a series of losses.

32:43.778 --> 32:47.464
Now, this is a guy who, I mean, he loved to be outdoors.

32:48.866 --> 32:50.248
And he loved to work in his garden.

32:50.288 --> 32:51.189
He loved to hunt.

32:51.209 --> 32:52.050
He loved to fish.

32:52.090 --> 32:54.354
I mean, his whole career, he was outdoors.

32:54.414 --> 32:57.899
And the last thing he wanted to do in life was to watch television.

33:01.304 --> 33:07.954
But it was like there was a series of losses that became unavoidable.

33:08.322 --> 33:11.367
Like some, you know, it's like a drip drip.

33:13.130 --> 33:22.905
And the truth is, this is going to happen for all of us, unless you die prematurely because it's a nature of the world we live in.

33:25.049 --> 33:35.666
So this drip drip drip that for him started out with my mom's loss and maybe the loss of a friend here or there, but that drip then became a stream.

33:36.642 --> 33:43.711
And that stream became a creek, and that creek finally became a river that was just impossible to cross.

33:45.553 --> 33:56.727
And he lost my mom, and he lost his friends, and he lost his health, and his life was finally compressed into just one chair in this one room where he watched TV all day, every day.

33:56.747 --> 34:02.034
I mean, the world took everything.

34:06.146 --> 34:14.899
Do you realize that that is the future most of your friends and coworkers have to face?

34:20.948 --> 34:25.194
But it's not the future that you have or that I have.

34:25.775 --> 34:36.050
Peter writes here, he says, blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ who according to his great mercy has caused us to be born again to a living hope.

34:36.194 --> 34:41.400
through the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead, to obtain an inheritance.

34:41.460 --> 34:42.301
Look at these words.

34:44.003 --> 34:55.115
See, because everything in this world, not just my dad's life, your life, everything you hold precious, everything is perishable.

34:56.436 --> 34:58.238
The world will ultimately take it.

34:59.680 --> 35:02.603
Everything will one day become defiled.

35:03.004 --> 35:05.266
Everything will one day

35:05.442 --> 35:06.383
fade away.

35:07.345 --> 35:15.415
But as Peter talks about our future, our inheritance, he says, there is a completely different class of reality here.

35:15.656 --> 35:20.522
There are things which are not perishable because they're not from this world.

35:20.743 --> 35:27.652
They are imperishable and they are undefined and they will never fade away.

35:27.672 --> 35:35.282
I mean, I love this quote, Tim Keller is a preacher in New York City and he has a quote

35:36.034 --> 35:51.271
On this subject, he says, if Jesus Christ was really raised from the dead and you believe in him, then all those things you long for, most desperately, are real and will come true.

35:52.432 --> 35:55.075
We will escape time and death.

35:56.617 --> 35:59.920
We will know love without party.

36:01.783 --> 36:04.946
Listen, for a child of God, the truth is that, yes,

36:05.346 --> 36:12.655
while the rest of the world, their backdrop is a cascading loss that finally takes everything from them.

36:13.777 --> 36:15.739
They might not like even to think about it.

36:15.759 --> 36:18.943
They don't want you to bring it up, maybe, but it's still true.

36:20.225 --> 36:23.990
But for you and for me, there will never be a moment.

36:24.030 --> 36:26.032
It doesn't matter what the world takes from you.

36:26.573 --> 36:27.795
It may take your friends.

36:27.875 --> 36:28.856
It may take your health.

36:28.996 --> 36:30.418
It may take your memories.

36:31.426 --> 36:37.812
But there will never be a nanosecond, a moment for you when the best is not yet to come.

36:40.495 --> 36:41.375
Is that good news?

36:43.137 --> 36:48.122
Do you know anybody in this world that doesn't need to hear and want to hear that news?

36:49.924 --> 36:50.504
Listen, folks.

36:55.309 --> 37:00.914
The most loving thing you can do in all the world with any person is to tell them the good news.

37:02.658 --> 37:09.368
Their lives are being lived against a backdrop that people, we don't even like to think about.

37:12.693 --> 37:13.654
You can give them hope.

37:16.238 --> 37:25.472
If you're here this morning, today is a day, I don't know what you thought before was a central message of the Christian church.

37:25.552 --> 37:28.136
Maybe you thought it was just behave yourself.

37:31.461 --> 37:32.402
But today is your day.

37:34.850 --> 37:37.653
You can embrace the hope that God has for you.

37:40.617 --> 37:41.418
Today is your day.

37:41.958 --> 37:47.264
You can embrace the forgiveness that God has made possible for you.

37:53.451 --> 38:02.642
You can embrace this God who is not just real or wise or powerful.

38:03.266 --> 38:05.549
not even just good, but amazingly good.

38:08.434 --> 38:11.759
And who has invited you to be his son or his daughter?

38:13.962 --> 38:17.247
Now then maybe somebody, maybe you've been a believer a long time.

38:17.307 --> 38:25.340
Maybe there's somebody you've been, I just haven't, I just can't get up the courage to speak to them about, look, do you love them?

38:28.945 --> 38:29.586
Do you love them?

38:32.642 --> 38:36.027
This is the best news our planet has ever heard.

38:38.010 --> 38:40.494
God's not just good, he is amazingly good.

38:42.257 --> 38:46.623
And that he has canceled the judgment that I deserve, he has canceled it forever.

38:49.187 --> 38:55.136
And that for me, or for the person that you love, they will never be a moment.

38:55.156 --> 39:00.224
If they know Jesus as their savior, they will never be a moment when the best is not yet to come.

39:00.825 --> 39:01.746
You can give them that.

39:03.810 --> 39:05.493
Let me ask you to bow your heads and close your eyes.

39:09.479 --> 39:11.422
In just a minute, I'm going to invite you to come.

39:11.442 --> 39:30.994
And if you're here this morning and today is the first day, and I know you've heard the words many times, but maybe today is the day that God has taken the scales off your eyes and you say, you know what, I need to embrace that, that hope, that forgiveness, that Savior.

39:33.378 --> 39:40.267
Or if you need to come this morning and just to kneel and pray for somebody that you love that needs to hear the gospel, ask God for that opportunity to share it, you come.

39:44.253 --> 39:46.656
Father, thank you for the truth of the gospel.

39:46.997 --> 39:57.471
Thank you for the privilege that we have of being your messengers and of loving the people around us enough to give them the best news this world has ever heard.

39:58.112 --> 40:02.738
Help us never, never, never to forget how awesome

40:03.810 --> 40:07.220
The gospel is, we pray in Jesus' name, amen.

40:08.023 --> 40:08.926
Let's all stand together.

40:08.946 --> 40:12.978
You come as God leads you this morning.

